==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[monachus]]'', from Greek ''[[monachos]]'' (monk, single person (not married)); confer Greek ''[[monos]]'' (one).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|monk|monks}}

# A person who is [[single]], that is, not [[married]].
# A person who lives alone; a [[hermit]].
# A person who lives in a [[religious]] [[community]] and usually under certain [[vow]]s such as [[poverty]], [[chastity]], [[obedience]], or [[stability]].

====Related terms====
*[[monastery]]
*[[monastic]]

